data.name: comboBox_Uplevel.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the upscaling level. If you specify 'x2', the output will be twice the pixels of the original image. If you specify 'x1', the output will be the same pixels as the original image. If you specify 'x2' or higher, it will be applied only when upscaling images. When upscaling video, it will be forced to 'x2' and will not be applied.

data.name: checkBox_TTA.ToolTip
data.value: Enables the TTA mode. Enabling this will improve the image index, but it takes a huge amount of time for image conversion.

data.name: comboBox_GPU.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the GPU to be used during conversion. If 'Auto' is specified, the GPU to be used will be determined automatically during conversion. If you specify 'iGPU', the conversion will be performed using the CPU's built-in graphics. (iGPU cannot be specified for CPUs that do not have built-in graphics.) If you have a multi-GPU environment, you can also specify either 'dGPU'.

data.name: checkBox_updetail.Text
data.value: Display image comparison dialog when upscaling is complete

data.name: comboBox_engine.ToolTip
data.value: Specify the conversion engine. waifu2x: Lower quality than Real-CUGAN and Real-ESRGAN, but faster. Real-CUGAN: Converts with much higher quality, but takes longer than waifu2x. Real-ESRGAN: Converts with much higher quality, but takes longer than waifu2x.

data.name: textBox_Blocksize.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the block size to be allocated to the GPU. If '0' is specified, the block size is automatically allocated. The larger the value, the faster the conversion will be, but the more memory the GPU will use. This item depends on the GPU performance, so if the value is too large, the conversion will fail.

data.name: checkBox_updetail.ToolTip
data.value: Displays an image comparison dialog when upscaling is complete. Normally enabled, but can be disabled to speed up the conversion process.

data.name: textBox_height.ToolTip
data.value: Specify the number of pixels in the image by height:width. This is useful, for example, when you want to output an upscaled image scaled down to a specified number of pixels. The aspect ratio of the image is preserved.

data.name: comboBox_Model.ToolTip
data.value: Specify the model to be used when upscaling. CUnet: This is selected by default. RGB: This model is suitable for upscaling illustrations. Photo: This model is suitable for upscaling photos.

data.name: textBox_width.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the pixels of the output image. Specify the number of pixels in the image by height:width. This is useful, for example, when you want to output an upscaled image scaled down to a specified number of pixels. The aspect ratio of the image is preserved.

data.name: checkBox_pixel.ToolTip
data.value: Enables the pixel specification item for the output image.

data.name: comboBox_Rdlevel.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the noise removal level of the image. If you specify 'No Reduction', the noise will not be removed. If you set the denoising level too high, details may be lost.

data.name: comboBox_Format.ToolTip
data.value: Specify the output format of the upscaled image. Normally '.png' is fine, but if you want to use a different format Change this field. If you select 'Custom', the format selection screen will appear when upscaling starts.

data.name: comboBox_Thread.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the number of threads used during conversion. The number of threads used can be assigned in the order 'load:proc:save'. This item can be changed only in a multi-GPU environment. Normally, specify '1:2:2'.

data.name: checkBox_Verbose.ToolTip
data.value: Enables verbose output. This option is for developers, so it is usually not necessary to enable it.

data.name: checkBox_destfolder.ToolTip
data.value: Displays the destination folder for upscaled images each time after completion. Normally enabled.
